HEADWORD: Monoclinal
<hw>Mon`o*cli"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Monoclinic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Having one oblique
inclination; -- applied to strata that dip in only one direction from
the axis of elevation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monocline</ent>⟦br⟧
